H2O is the water density (in g/cm3), ∆T (in s) is the acquisition time, LET
k (in keV/µm) is the measured LET of the kth particle and 1.6 is a numeric factor producing the Dose rate in nGy/s. The 4π coefficient comes from the integration over the full solid angle. The geometrical factor GF contains all the information about the geometry of the detector and it is used to estimate the radiation flux, assuming source isotropy.

